1 /*
2 ** ###################################################################
3 ** Processors: MK60DN512ZVLL10
4 ** MK60DX256ZVLL10
5 ** MK60DN256ZVLL10
6 ** MK60DN512ZVLQ10
7 ** MK60DN256ZVLQ10
8 ** MK60DX256ZVLQ10
9 ** MK60DN512ZVMC10
10 ** MK60DN256ZVMC10
11 ** MK60DX256ZVMC10
12 ** MK60DN512ZVMD10
13 ** MK60DX256ZVMD10
14 ** MK60DN256ZVMD10
15 **
16 ** Compilers: ARM Compiler
17 ** Freescale C/C++ for Embedded ARM
18 ** GNU C Compiler
19 ** IAR ANSI C/C++ Compiler for ARM
20 **
21 ** Reference manual: K60P144M100SF2RM, Rev. 5, 8 May 2011
22 ** Version: rev. 1.2, 2011-09-08
23 **
24 ** Abstract:
25 ** CMSIS Peripheral Access Layer for MK60DZ10
26 **
27 ** Copyright: 1997 - 2011 Freescale Semiconductor, Inc. All Rights Reserved.
28 **
29 ** http: www.freescale.com
30 ** mail: support@freescale.com
31 **
32 ** Revisions:
33 ** - rev. 1.0 (2011-06-10)
34 ** Initial version.
35 ** Changes with respect to the previous MK60NxxxMD100 header file:
36 ** RTC - CCR register removed. Replaced by IER register.
37 ** CRC - added CTRLHU register for 8-bit access to the CTRL register.
38 ** FB - bit FB_CSCR_EXALE renamed to FB_CSCR_EXTS.
39 ** SIM - bit group FSIZE in SIM_FCFG1 split into groups PFSIZE and NVMSIZE.
40 ** I2S - bit SSIEN in I2S_CR register renamed to I2SEN.
41 ** SDHC - bit VOLTSEL in SDHC_VENDOR register removed.
42 ** - rev. 1.1 (2011-06-29)
43 ** Order of declarations changed.
44 ** - rev. 1.2 (2011-09-08)
45 ** Cortex_Core_Configuration extended with additional parameters.
46 ** Gap between end of interrupt vector table and flash configuration field filled by default ISR.
47 **
48 ** ###################################################################
49 */
50

66 /**
67  * @brief Macro to access a single bit of a peripheral register (bit band region
68  * 0x40000000 to 0x400FFFFF) using the bit-band alias region access.
69  * @param Reg Register to access.
70  * @param Bit Bit number to access.
71  * @return Value of the targeted bit in the bit band region.
72  */
73 #define BITBAND_REG(Reg,Bit) (*((uint32_t volatile*)(0x42000000u + (32u*((uint32_t)&(Reg) - (uint32_t)0x40000000u)) + (4u*((uint32_t)(Bit))))))

268 /** ADC - Register Layout Typedef */
269 typedef struct {
270  __IO uint32_t SC1[2]; /**< ADC status and control registers 1, array offset: 0x0, array step: 0x4 */
271  __IO uint32_t CFG1; /**< ADC configuration register 1, offset: 0x8 */
272  __IO uint32_t CFG2; /**< Configuration register 2, offset: 0xC */
273  __I uint32_t R[2]; /**< ADC data result register, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x4 */
274  __IO uint32_t CV1; /**< Compare value registers, offset: 0x18 */
275  __IO uint32_t CV2; /**< Compare value registers, offset: 0x1C */
276  __IO uint32_t SC2; /**< Status and control register 2, offset: 0x20 */
277  __IO uint32_t SC3; /**< Status and control register 3, offset: 0x24 */
278  __IO uint32_t OFS; /**< ADC offset correction register, offset: 0x28 */
279  __IO uint32_t PG; /**< ADC plus-side gain register, offset: 0x2C */
280  __IO uint32_t MG; /**< ADC minus-side gain register, offset: 0x30 */
281  __IO uint32_t CLPD; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x34 */
282  __IO uint32_t CLPS; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x38 */
283  __IO uint32_t CLP4; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x3C */
284  __IO uint32_t CLP3; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x40 */
285  __IO uint32_t CLP2; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x44 */
286  __IO uint32_t CLP1; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x48 */
287  __IO uint32_t CLP0; /**< ADC plus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x4C */
288  __IO uint32_t PGA; /**< ADC PGA register, offset: 0x50 */
289  __IO uint32_t CLMD; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x54 */
290  __IO uint32_t CLMS; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x58 */
291  __IO uint32_t CLM4; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x5C */
292  __IO uint32_t CLM3; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x60 */
293  __IO uint32_t CLM2; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x64 */
294  __IO uint32_t CLM1; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x68 */
295  __IO uint32_t CLM0; /**< ADC minus-side general calibration value register, offset: 0x6C */
296 } ADC_Type;

307 /* SC1 Bit Fields */

309 #define ADC_SC1_ADCH_SHIFT 0
310 #define ADC_SC1_ADCH(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_SC1_ADCH_SHIFT))&ADC_SC1_ADCH_MASK)
311 #define ADC_SC1_DIFF_MASK 0x20u
312 #define ADC_SC1_DIFF_SHIFT 5
313 #define ADC_SC1_AIEN_MASK 0x40u
314 #define ADC_SC1_AIEN_SHIFT 6
315 #define ADC_SC1_COCO_MASK 0x80u
316 #define ADC_SC1_COCO_SHIFT 7
317 /* CFG1 Bit Fields */
318 #define ADC_CFG1_ADICLK_MASK 0x3u
319 #define ADC_CFG1_ADICLK_SHIFT 0
320 #define ADC_CFG1_ADICLK(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CFG1_ADICLK_SHIFT))&ADC_CFG1_ADICLK_MASK)
321 #define ADC_CFG1_MODE_MASK 0xCu
322 #define ADC_CFG1_MODE_SHIFT 2
323 #define ADC_CFG1_MODE(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CFG1_MODE_SHIFT))&ADC_CFG1_MODE_MASK)
324 #define ADC_CFG1_ADLSMP_MASK 0x10u
325 #define ADC_CFG1_ADLSMP_SHIFT 4
326 #define ADC_CFG1_ADIV_MASK 0x60u
327 #define ADC_CFG1_ADIV_SHIFT 5
328 #define ADC_CFG1_ADIV(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CFG1_ADIV_SHIFT))&ADC_CFG1_ADIV_MASK)
329 #define ADC_CFG1_ADLPC_MASK 0x80u
330 #define ADC_CFG1_ADLPC_SHIFT 7
331 /* CFG2 Bit Fields */

446 #define ADC_CLM2_CLM2(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CLM2_CLM2_SHIFT))&ADC_CLM2_CLM2_MASK)
447 /* CLM1 Bit Fields */
448 #define ADC_CLM1_CLM1_MASK 0x7Fu
449 #define ADC_CLM1_CLM1_SHIFT 0
450 #define ADC_CLM1_CLM1(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CLM1_CLM1_SHIFT))&ADC_CLM1_CLM1_MASK)
451 /* CLM0 Bit Fields */
452 #define ADC_CLM0_CLM0_MASK 0x3Fu
453 #define ADC_CLM0_CLM0_SHIFT 0
454 #define ADC_CLM0_CLM0(x) (((uint32_t)(((uint32_t)(x))<<ADC_CLM0_CLM0_SHIFT))&ADC_CLM0_CLM0_MASK)
455 
456 /**
457  * @}
458  */ /* end of group ADC_Register_Masks */
459 
460 
461 /* ADC - Peripheral instance base addresses */
462 /** Peripheral ADC0 base address */
463 #define ADC0_BASE (0x4003B000u)
464 /** Peripheral ADC0 base pointer */
465 #define ADC0 ((ADC_Type *)ADC0_BASE)
466 /** Peripheral ADC1 base address */
467 #define ADC1_BASE (0x400BB000u)
468 /** Peripheral ADC1 base pointer */
469 #define ADC1 ((ADC_Type *)ADC1_BASE)
470 
471 /**
472  * @}
473  */ /* end of group ADC_Peripheral_Access_Layer */

478  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- */

480 /**
481  * @addtogroup AIPS_Peripheral_Access_Layer AIPS Peripheral Access Layer
482  * @{
483  */
484 
485 /** AIPS - Register Layout Typedef */
486 typedef struct {
487  __IO uint32_t MPRA; /**< Master Privilege Register A, offset: 0x0 */
488  uint8_t RESERVED_0[28];
489  __IO uint32_t PACRA; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x20 */
490  __IO uint32_t PACRB; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x24 */
491  __IO uint32_t PACRC; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x28 */
492  __IO uint32_t PACRD; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x2C */
493  uint8_t RESERVED_1[16];
494  __IO uint32_t PACRE; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x40 */
495  __IO uint32_t PACRF; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x44 */
496  __IO uint32_t PACRG; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x48 */
497  __IO uint32_t PACRH; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x4C */
498  __IO uint32_t PACRI; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x50 */
499  __IO uint32_t PACRJ; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x54 */
500  __IO uint32_t PACRK; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x58 */
501  __IO uint32_t PACRL; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x5C */
502  __IO uint32_t PACRM; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x60 */
503  __IO uint32_t PACRN; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x64 */
504  __IO uint32_t PACRO; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x68 */
505  __IO uint32_t PACRP; /**< Peripheral Access Control Register, offset: 0x6C */
506 } AIPS_Type;

1504  struct { /* offset: 0x80, array step: 0x10 */
1505  __IO uint32_t CS; /**< Message Buffer 0 CS Register..Message Buffer 15 CS Register, array offset: 0x80, array step: 0x10 */
1506  __IO uint32_t ID; /**< Message Buffer 0 ID Register..Message Buffer 15 ID Register, array offset: 0x84, array step: 0x10 */
1507  __IO uint32_t WORD0; /**< Message Buffer 0 WORD0 Register..Message Buffer 15 WORD0 Register, array offset: 0x88, array step: 0x10 */
1508  __IO uint32_t WORD1; /**< Message Buffer 0 WORD1 Register..Message Buffer 15 WORD1 Register, array offset: 0x8C, array step: 0x10 */
1509  } MB[16];

1512 } CAN_Type;

2442 typedef struct {

2452  __O uint8_t SERQ; /**< Set Enable Request Register, offset: 0x1B */

2454  __O uint8_t SSRT; /**< Set START Bit Register, offset: 0x1D */
2455  __O uint8_t CERR; /**< Clear Error Register, offset: 0x1E */
2456  __O uint8_t CINT; /**< Clear Interrupt Request Register, offset: 0x1F */

2478  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI13; /**< Channel n Priority Register, offset: 0x10E */
2479  __IO uint8_t DCHPRI12; /**< Channel n Priority Register, offset: 0x10F */
2480  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3824];
2481  struct { /* offset: 0x1000, array step: 0x20 */
2482  __IO uint32_t SADDR; /**< TCD Source Address, array offset: 0x1000, array step: 0x20 */
2483  __IO uint16_t SOFF; /**< TCD Signed Source Address Offset, array offset: 0x1004, array step: 0x20 */
2484  __IO uint16_t ATTR; /**< TCD Transfer Attributes, array offset: 0x1006, array step: 0x20 */
2485  union { /* offset: 0x1008, array step: 0x20 */
2486  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLNO; /**< TCD Minor Byte Count (Minor Loop Disabled), array offset: 0x1008, array step: 0x20 */
2487  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLOFFNO; /**< TCD Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop Enabled and Offset Disabled), array offset: 0x1008, array step: 0x20 */
2488  __IO uint32_t NBYTES_MLOFFYES; /**< TCD Signed Minor Loop Offset (Minor Loop and Offset Enabled), array offset: 0x1008, array step: 0x20 */
2489  };
2490  __IO uint32_t SLAST; /**< TCD Last Source Address Adjustment, array offset: 0x100C, array step: 0x20 */
2491  __IO uint32_t DADDR; /**< TCD Destination Address, array offset: 0x1010, array step: 0x20 */
2492  __IO uint16_t DOFF; /**< TCD Signed Destination Address Offset, array offset: 0x1014, array step: 0x20 */
2493  union { /* offset: 0x1016, array step: 0x20 */
2494  __IO uint16_t CITER_ELINKNO; /**< TCD Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled), array offset: 0x1016, array step: 0x20 */
2495  __IO uint16_t CITER_ELINKYES; /**< TCD Current Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled), array offset: 0x1016, array step: 0x20 */
2496  };
2497  __IO uint32_t DLAST_SGA; /**< TCD Last Destination Address Adjustment/Scatter Gather Address, array offset: 0x1018, array step: 0x20 */
2498  __IO uint16_t CSR; /**< TCD Control and Status, array offset: 0x101C, array step: 0x20 */
2499  union { /* offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */
2500  __IO uint16_t BITER_ELINKNO; /**< TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Disabled), array offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */
2501  __IO uint16_t BITER_ELINKYES; /**< TCD Beginning Minor Loop Link, Major Loop Count (Channel Linking Enabled), array offset: 0x101E, array step: 0x20 */
2502  };
2503  } TCD[16];
2504 } DMA_Type;

3198  __IO uint32_t RMON_R_DROP; /**< Count of frames not counted correctly (IEEE_R_DROP). NOTE: Counter increments if a frame with valid/missing SFD character is detected and has been dropped. None of the other counters increments if this counter increments., offset: 0x2C8 */

4108  __IO uint32_t SYNC; /**< Synchronization, offset: 0x58 */

4116  __IO uint32_t FILTER; /**< Input Capture Filter Control, offset: 0x78 */

4572 
4573 /** GPIO - Register Layout Typedef */
4574 typedef struct {
4575  __IO uint32_t PDOR; /**< Port Data Output Register, offset: 0x0 */
4576  __O uint32_t PSOR; /**< Port Set Output Register, offset: 0x4 */
4577  __O uint32_t PCOR; /**< Port Clear Output Register, offset: 0x8 */
4578  __O uint32_t PTOR; /**< Port Toggle Output Register, offset: 0xC */
4579  __I uint32_t PDIR; /**< Port Data Input Register, offset: 0x10 */
4580  __IO uint32_t PDDR; /**< Port Data Direction Register, offset: 0x14 */
4581 } GPIO_Type;

6077  __IO uint32_t C1; /**< Channel n Control Register 1, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x28 */
6078  __IO uint32_t S; /**< Channel n Status Register, array offset: 0x14, array step: 0x28 */
6079  __IO uint32_t DLY[2]; /**< Channel n Delay 0 Register..Channel n Delay 1 Register, array offset: 0x18, array step: index*0x28, index2*0x4 */
6080  uint8_t RESERVED_0[24];
6081  } CH[2];
6082  uint8_t RESERVED_0[240];
6083  struct { /* offset: 0x150, array step: 0x8 */
6084  __IO uint32_t INTC; /**< DAC Interval Trigger n Control Register, array offset: 0x150, array step: 0x8 */
6085  __IO uint32_t INT; /**< DAC Interval n Register, array offset: 0x154, array step: 0x8 */
6086  } DAC[2];
6087  uint8_t RESERVED_1[48];
6088  __IO uint32_t POEN; /**< Pulse-Out n Enable Register, offset: 0x190 */
6089  __IO uint32_t PODLY; /**< Pulse-Out n Delay Register, offset: 0x194 */
6090 } PDB_Type;

6690 /** RTC - Register Layout Typedef */
6691 typedef struct {
6692  __IO uint32_t TSR; /**< RTC Time Seconds Register, offset: 0x0 */
6693  __IO uint32_t TPR; /**< RTC Time Prescaler Register, offset: 0x4 */
6694  __IO uint32_t TAR; /**< RTC Time Alarm Register, offset: 0x8 */
6695  __IO uint32_t TCR; /**< RTC Time Compensation Register, offset: 0xC */
6696  __IO uint32_t CR; /**< RTC Control Register, offset: 0x10 */
6697  __IO uint32_t SR; /**< RTC Status Register, offset: 0x14 */
6698  __IO uint32_t LR; /**< RTC Lock Register, offset: 0x18 */
6699  __IO uint32_t IER; /**< RTC Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x1C */
6700  uint8_t RESERVED_0[2016];
6701  __IO uint32_t WAR; /**< RTC Write Access Register, offset: 0x800 */
6702  __IO uint32_t RAR; /**< RTC Read Access Register, offset: 0x804 */
6703 } RTC_Type;

6845 /** SDHC - Register Layout Typedef */
6846 typedef struct {
6847  __IO uint32_t DSADDR; /**< DMA System Address Register, offset: 0x0 */
6848  __IO uint32_t BLKATTR; /**< Block Attributes Register, offset: 0x4 */
6849  __IO uint32_t CMDARG; /**< Command Argument Register, offset: 0x8 */
6850  __IO uint32_t XFERTYP; /**< Transfer Type Register, offset: 0xC */
6851  __I uint32_t CMDRSP[4]; /**< Command Response 0..Command Response 3, array offset: 0x10, array step: 0x4 */
6852  __IO uint32_t DATPORT; /**< Buffer Data Port Register, offset: 0x20 */
6853  __I uint32_t PRSSTAT; /**< Present State Register, offset: 0x24 */
6854  __IO uint32_t PROCTL; /**< Protocol Control Register, offset: 0x28 */
6855  __IO uint32_t SYSCTL; /**< System Control Register, offset: 0x2C */
6856  __IO uint32_t IRQSTAT; /**< Interrupt Status Register, offset: 0x30 */
6857  __IO uint32_t IRQSTATEN; /**< Interrupt Status Enable Register, offset: 0x34 */
6858  __IO uint32_t IRQSIGEN; /**< Interrupt Signal Enable Register, offset: 0x38 */
6859  __I uint32_t AC12ERR; /**< Auto CMD12 Error Status Register, offset: 0x3C */
6860  __I uint32_t HTCAPBLT; /**< Host Controller Capabilities, offset: 0x40 */
6861  __IO uint32_t WML; /**< Watermark Level Register, offset: 0x44 */
6862  uint8_t RESERVED_0[8];
6863  __O uint32_t FEVT; /**< Force Event Register, offset: 0x50 */
6864  __I uint32_t ADMAES; /**< ADMA Error Status Register, offset: 0x54 */
6865  __IO uint32_t ADSADDR; /**< ADMA System Address Register, offset: 0x58 */
6866  uint8_t RESERVED_1[100];
6867  __IO uint32_t VENDOR; /**< Vendor Specific Register, offset: 0xC0 */
6868  __IO uint32_t MMCBOOT; /**< MMC Boot Register, offset: 0xC4 */
6869  uint8_t RESERVED_2[52];
6870  __I uint32_t HOSTVER; /**< Host Controller Version, offset: 0xFC */
6871 } SDHC_Type;

7283 /** SIM - Register Layout Typedef */
7284 typedef struct {
7285  __IO uint32_t SOPT1; /**< System Options Register 1, offset: 0x0 */
7286  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4096];
7287  __IO uint32_t SOPT2; /**< System Options Register 2, offset: 0x1004 */
7288  uint8_t RESERVED_1[4];
7289  __IO uint32_t SOPT4; /**< System Options Register 4, offset: 0x100C */
7290  __IO uint32_t SOPT5; /**< System Options Register 5, offset: 0x1010 */
7291  __IO uint32_t SOPT6; /**< System Options Register 6, offset: 0x1014 */
7292  __IO uint32_t SOPT7; /**< System Options Register 7, offset: 0x1018 */
7293  uint8_t RESERVED_2[8];
7294  __I uint32_t SDID; /**< System Device Identification Register, offset: 0x1024 */
7295  __IO uint32_t SCGC1; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 1, offset: 0x1028 */
7296  __IO uint32_t SCGC2; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 2, offset: 0x102C */
7297  __IO uint32_t SCGC3; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 3, offset: 0x1030 */
7298  __IO uint32_t SCGC4; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 4, offset: 0x1034 */
7299  __IO uint32_t SCGC5; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 5, offset: 0x1038 */
7300  __IO uint32_t SCGC6; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 6, offset: 0x103C */
7301  __IO uint32_t SCGC7; /**< System Clock Gating Control Register 7, offset: 0x1040 */
7302  __IO uint32_t CLKDIV1; /**< System Clock Divider Register 1, offset: 0x1044 */
7303  __IO uint32_t CLKDIV2; /**< System Clock Divider Register 2, offset: 0x1048 */
7304  __I uint32_t FCFG1; /**< Flash Configuration Register 1, offset: 0x104C */
7305  __I uint32_t FCFG2; /**< Flash Configuration Register 2, offset: 0x1050 */
7306  __I uint32_t UIDH; /**< Unique Identification Register High, offset: 0x1054 */
7307  __I uint32_t UIDMH; /**< Unique Identification Register Mid-High, offset: 0x1058 */
7308  __I uint32_t UIDML; /**< Unique Identification Register Mid Low, offset: 0x105C */
7309  __I uint32_t UIDL; /**< Unique Identification Register Low, offset: 0x1060 */
7310 } SIM_Type;

7609 /* ----------------------------------------------------------------------------
7610  -- SPI Peripheral Access Layer
7611  ---------------------------------------------------------------------------- */
7612 
7613 /**
7614  * @addtogroup SPI_Peripheral_Access_Layer SPI Peripheral Access Layer
7615  * @{
7616  */
7617 
7618 /** SPI - Register Layout Typedef */
7619 typedef struct {
7620  __IO uint32_t MCR; /**< DSPI Module Configuration Register, offset: 0x0 */
7621  uint8_t RESERVED_0[4];
7622  __IO uint32_t TCR; /**< DSPI Transfer Count Register, offset: 0x8 */
7623  union { /* offset: 0xC */
7624  __IO uint32_t CTAR[2]; /**< DSPI Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Master Mode), array offset: 0xC, array step: 0x4 */
7625  __IO uint32_t CTAR_SLAVE[1]; /**< DSPI Clock and Transfer Attributes Register (In Slave Mode), array offset: 0xC, array step: 0x4 */
7626  };
7627  uint8_t RESERVED_1[24];
7628  __IO uint32_t SR; /**< DSPI Status Register, offset: 0x2C */
7629  __IO uint32_t RSER; /**< DSPI DMA/Interrupt Request Select and Enable Register, offset: 0x30 */
7630  union { /* offset: 0x34 */
7631  __IO uint32_t PUSHR; /**< DSPI PUSH TX FIFO Register In Master Mode, offset: 0x34 */
7632  __IO uint32_t PUSHR_SLAVE; /**< DSPI PUSH TX FIFO Register In Slave Mode, offset: 0x34 */
7633  };
7634  __I uint32_t POPR; /**< DSPI POP RX FIFO Register, offset: 0x38 */
7635  __I uint32_t TXFR0; /**< DSPI Transmit FIFO Registers, offset: 0x3C */
7636  __I uint32_t TXFR1; /**< DSPI Transmit FIFO Registers, offset: 0x40 */
7637  __I uint32_t TXFR2; /**< DSPI Transmit FIFO Registers, offset: 0x44 */
7638  __I uint32_t TXFR3; /**< DSPI Transmit FIFO Registers, offset: 0x48 */
7639  uint8_t RESERVED_2[48];
7640  __I uint32_t RXFR0; /**< DSPI Receive FIFO Registers, offset: 0x7C */
7641  __I uint32_t RXFR1; /**< DSPI Receive FIFO Registers, offset: 0x80 */
7642  __I uint32_t RXFR2; /**< DSPI Receive FIFO Registers, offset: 0x84 */
7643  __I uint32_t RXFR3; /**< DSPI Receive FIFO Registers, offset: 0x88 */
7644 } SPI_Type;
7645

7880 /**
7881  * @addtogroup TSI_Peripheral_Access_Layer TSI Peripheral Access Layer
7882  * @{
7883  */
7884 
7885 /** TSI - Register Layout Typedef */
7886 typedef struct {
7887  __IO uint32_t GENCS; /**< General Control and Status Register, offset: 0x0 */
7888  __IO uint32_t SCANC; /**< SCAN control register, offset: 0x4 */
7889  __IO uint32_t PEN; /**< Pin enable register, offset: 0x8 */
7890  __IO uint32_t STATUS; /**< Status Register, offset: 0xC */
7891  uint8_t RESERVED_0[240];
7892  __I uint32_t CNTR1; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x100 */
7893  __I uint32_t CNTR3; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x104 */
7894  __I uint32_t CNTR5; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x108 */
7895  __I uint32_t CNTR7; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x10C */
7896  __I uint32_t CNTR9; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x110 */
7897  __I uint32_t CNTR11; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x114 */
7898  __I uint32_t CNTR13; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x118 */
7899  __I uint32_t CNTR15; /**< Counter Register, offset: 0x11C */
7900  __IO uint32_t THRESHLD[16]; /**< Channel n threshold register, array offset: 0x120, array step: 0x4 */
7901 } TSI_Type;

8134 #define TSI_THRESHLD_LTHH_SHIFT 16

8162 /** UART - Register Layout Typedef */
8163 typedef struct {
8164  __IO uint8_t BDH; /**< UART Baud Rate Registers:High, offset: 0x0 */
8165  __IO uint8_t BDL; /**< UART Baud Rate Registers: Low, offset: 0x1 */
8166  __IO uint8_t C1; /**< UART Control Register 1, offset: 0x2 */
8167  __IO uint8_t C2; /**< UART Control Register 2, offset: 0x3 */
8168  __I uint8_t S1; /**< UART Status Register 1, offset: 0x4 */
8169  __IO uint8_t S2; /**< UART Status Register 2, offset: 0x5 */
8170  __IO uint8_t C3; /**< UART Control Register 3, offset: 0x6 */
8171  __IO uint8_t D; /**< UART Data Register, offset: 0x7 */
8172  __IO uint8_t MA1; /**< UART Match Address Registers 1, offset: 0x8 */
8173  __IO uint8_t MA2; /**< UART Match Address Registers 2, offset: 0x9 */
8174  __IO uint8_t C4; /**< UART Control Register 4, offset: 0xA */
8175  __IO uint8_t C5; /**< UART Control Register 5, offset: 0xB */
8176  __I uint8_t ED; /**< UART Extended Data Register, offset: 0xC */
8177  __IO uint8_t MODEM; /**< UART Modem Register, offset: 0xD */
8178  __IO uint8_t IR; /**< UART Infrared Register, offset: 0xE */
8179  uint8_t RESERVED_0[1];
8180  __IO uint8_t PFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Parameters, offset: 0x10 */
8181  __IO uint8_t CFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Control Register, offset: 0x11 */
8182  __IO uint8_t SFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Status Register, offset: 0x12 */
8183  __IO uint8_t TWFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Transmit Watermark, offset: 0x13 */
8184  __I uint8_t TCFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Transmit Count, offset: 0x14 */
8185  __IO uint8_t RWFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Receive Watermark, offset: 0x15 */
8186  __I uint8_t RCFIFO; /**< UART FIFO Receive Count, offset: 0x16 */
8187  uint8_t RESERVED_1[1];
8188  __IO uint8_t C7816; /**< UART 7816 Control Register, offset: 0x18 */
8189  __IO uint8_t IE7816; /**< UART 7816 Interrupt Enable Register, offset: 0x19 */
8190  __IO uint8_t IS7816; /**< UART 7816 Interrupt Status Register, offset: 0x1A */
8191  union { /* offset: 0x1B */
8192  __IO uint8_t WP7816_T_TYPE0; /**< UART 7816 Wait Parameter Register, offset: 0x1B */
8193  __IO uint8_t WP7816_T_TYPE1; /**< UART 7816 Wait Parameter Register, offset: 0x1B */
8194  };
8195  __IO uint8_t WN7816; /**< UART 7816 Wait N Register, offset: 0x1C */
8196  __IO uint8_t WF7816; /**< UART 7816 Wait FD Register, offset: 0x1D */
8197  __IO uint8_t ET7816; /**< UART 7816 Error Threshold Register, offset: 0x1E */
8198  __IO uint8_t TL7816; /**< UART 7816 Transmit Length Register, offset: 0x1F */
8199 } UART_Type;

8529  uint8_t RESERVED_5[3];

8531  uint8_t RESERVED_6[3];

8543  uint8_t RESERVED_12[3];
8544  __IO uint8_t CTL; /**< Control Register, offset: 0x94 */

8560  __IO uint8_t BDTPAGE3; /**< BDT Page Register 3, offset: 0xB4 */
8561  uint8_t RESERVED_21[11];
8562  struct { /* offset: 0xC0, array step: 0x4 */
8563  __IO uint8_t ENDPT; /**< Endpoint Control Register, array offset: 0xC0, array step: 0x4 */
8564  uint8_t RESERVED_0[3];
8565  } ENDPOINT[16];
8566  __IO uint8_t USBCTRL; /**< USB Control Register, offset: 0x100 */
8567  uint8_t RESERVED_22[3];
8568  __I uint8_t OBSERVE; /**< USB OTG Observe Register, offset: 0x104 */
8569  uint8_t RESERVED_23[3];
8570  __IO uint8_t CONTROL; /**< USB OTG Control Register, offset: 0x108 */
8571  uint8_t RESERVED_24[3];
8572  __IO uint8_t USBTRC0; /**< USB Transceiver Control Register 0, offset: 0x10C */
8573 } USB_Type;
